documentation.text:
@dev Contract module which provides a basic access control mechanism, where
 there is an account (an owner) that can be granted exclusive access to
 specific functions.
 By default, the owner account will be the one that deploys the contract. This
 can later be changed with {transferOwnership}.
@dev Initializes the contract setting the deployer as the initial owner.

devdoc.details: Contract module which provides a basic access control mechanism, where there is an account (an owner) that can be granted exclusive access to specific functions. By default, the owner account will be the one that deploys the contract. This can later be changed with {transferOwnership}.

addWhitelistedAdmin(address).details: Add new Admin to _whitelistedAdmin mapping. Can only be called by the current owner and existing admin.

admin(address).details: Return `true` if the @param _address is the whitelistedAdmin else `false`.

checkAdmin(address).details: Return `true` if the @param _address is the whitelistedAdmin else `revert`.

checkOwner(address).details: Return `true` if the @param _address is the owner else `revert`.

constructor.details: Initializes the contract setting the deployer as the initial owner.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

removeWhitelistedAdmin(address).details: Remove existing Admin from _whitelistedAdmin mapping. Can only be called by the current owner and existing admin. Existing admin will not able to remove him/her self form _whitelistedAdmin mapping.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.
